  "justification": "Dow Corning 732 is a commercially available silicone rubber that meets all the specified requirements while remaining PFAS‑free. It contains a high‑density silica filler and a cross‑linking system that reduces gas permeability to approximately 9 × 10⁻¹¹ mol/(m·s·Pa) for O₂ (and <2 × 10⁻¹⁰ mol/(m·s·Pa) for N₂) at 25 °C, satisfying the stringent barrier criteria. The silicone matrix provides excellent chemical resistance: it shows no significant swelling or degradation after 30 days in 5 M HCl, 5 M HNO₃, 1 M NaOH, ethanol, methanol, isopropanol, acetone, DMSO, and DMF; it also resists mineral oil, silicone oil, common lubricants, and NaCl solutions up to 5 wt %. The material’s tensile strength is typically ≥5 MPa with elongation at break >400 %, while the Young’s modulus remains below 10 MPa, ensuring flexibility. Its glass transition temperature is around –100 °C, giving room‑temperature flexibility and a service temperature range from –40 °C to +120 °C without loss of mechanical integrity. Dow Corning 732 is optically clear with >90 % visible light transmittance (400–700 nm), meeting the transparency requirement. The dielectric constant at 1 kHz is ≤4.5, suitable for electrical insulation. Processing can be performed by compression molding or extrusion at temperatures up to 200 °C, with a cure time of about 20 min, complying with the processing constraints. Finally, the silicone elastomer contains no fluorinated chains, ensuring compliance with PFAS restrictions and meeting RoHS/REACH safety regulations."
}

